CORE INFRASTRUCTURE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- Electron + React + TypeScript desktop app
- SQLite database (database.ts) with base tables:
  teams, players, games, stats, contracts, settings, champions,
  draft_prospects, depth_chart, career_stats_history, hall_of_fame,
  historical_records, news_events, pick_assets, team_trade_overrides,
  player_milestones, dead_cap_entries, coaching_staff, team_schemes,
  owner_goals
- Schema version: v12. Migration runner in runMigrations() upgrades existing
  saves on launch. Old migration blocks removed once all saves have passed them.
  Active migrations:
    v9: team_id INTEGER on career_stats_history + idx_career_stats_team
    v10: Recalibrate all active-roster contract salaries to market-rate scale
         (fixes "TEAM DEAL" badge on nearly every player from prior saves)
    v11: Normalize all team salary totals to 95% of salary cap (~$265M),
         proportionally scaling each team's roster for equal cap distribution
    v12: owner_goals table (season, goal_type, target_value, achieved);
         owner_patience setting initialized to 75
- generateContracts() uses CONTRACT_MARKET_RATES table (positions QB/WR/DL/CB/
  OL/LB/TE/S/RB/K, breakpoints OVR 70–99) + TRAIT_PREMIUM multipliers to
  generate realistic per-player salaries. After generation, every team is
  proportionally scaled so total payroll lands at exactly 95% of SALARY_CAP
  (~$265M), giving all 32 teams equal cap standing at dynasty start.
- career_stats_history columns: player_id, season, team_id, games,
  completions, pass/rush/rec stats, defensive stats, def_tds.
  team_id captures the team the player accumulated stats for that season
  (archived via MAX(s.team_id) at season-end).
- DB indexes:
    stats: game_id, player_id, team_id, (team_id,game_id), (season,is_playoff)
    games: season, (season,is_simulated), (season,week,is_playoff)
    career_stats_history: player_id, (player_id,season), team_id
    news_events: (season,week), (season,category)
    contracts: team_id, player_id
    depth_chart: (team_id,position_group)
    pick_assets: (owner_team_id,season)
    draft_prospects: season
    players: (team_id,roster_status), roster_status
- player_milestones table — deduplication store with PRIMARY KEY
  (player_id, milestone_key)
- 32 fictional teams auto-seeded on first launch (AFC/NFC, 4 divisions each)
- Fictional player generator: 53 players per team + 176 free agents on fresh
  start (position-specific attributes, dev trait distribution, OVR curves)
- Multiple save files — save picker at launch, lazy DB init via Proxy,
  full save create / load / delete UI (SavePicker.tsx + saveHandlers.ts)
- Reset save / new dynasty supported
- Season advance prunes: news_events kept to last 3 seasons; raw stats table
  kept to current + prior season (older data archived to career_stats_history)

